headline.main: Use of Mediterranean Not Vital to Britain, But Longer Route Will Strain Her Economy

lead_paragraph: The Mediterranean shipping lanes are not as they have been called, Britain's life line. They are important, but not vital to British commerce and economy. They are of greater importance strategically and from the viewpoint of prestige.
